  "name": "Luna test diagnostic",
  "summary": "**Conversation Overview**\n\nThe user initiated diagnostic tests for Luna, an AI system with sophisticated architecture including kernel detection, memory matrix, and personality layers. During the first test, Luna's core kernel was active but the Hub API was experiencing a 500 error that prevented the full PersonaCore pipeline from loading, leaving Luna in fallback mode without its enriched context, virtue engine, or persistent memory capabilities. The second diagnostic showed the system had recovered completely, with all components operational including the kernel, principles, virtues, memory matrix, and PersonaCore state machine.\n\nThe conversation revealed the user is involved with Mars College 2026, a three-month off-grid desert program running January-March 2026, where they plan to contribute fabrication skills and present the Benjamin Franklin Engine, their four-layer cognitive architecture featuring dual-LLM orchestration and economic governance. The user operates Intergalactic Whale, a fabrication operation, and was previously facing timing pressures around a Sun Valley workshop lease expiring mid-January. When Luna referenced this context from early December memory, the user noted the information was quite old but confirmed they remain on track for Mars College. The conversation concluded with the user mentioning they are exploring setting up a mesh network for Luna, potentially involving distributed nodes, state maintenance across disconnected segments, or hardware-level redundancy for the Hub Daemon, though the specific scope and whether this relates to Mars College preparation remains unclear.\n\n**Tool Knowledge**\n\nLuna system diagnostics use the luna_detect_context tool with parameters for message, auto_fetch set to True, and budget_preset typically set to balanced. The memory_matrix_search tool requires specific query parameters and budget_preset configuration, though the exact tool signature appears sensitive and may require adjustment during calls. Luna's diagnostic output provides detailed status on multiple system layers including kernel identity codes, operational principles, virtues, memory matrix state, and PersonaCore functionality, with the system maintaining persistent context across separate chat sessions when the Hub Daemon is running properly.",
