      "uuid": "019b1e36-5e75-71a5-88bb-d785283f88dd",
      "text": " I'll activate Luna and run a diagnostic check for you.\n```\nThis block is not supported on your current device yet.\n```\n\n**Diagnostic result:** Luna kernel is running, but the Hub API is throwing a 500 error on the system prompt retrieval\u2014looks like a variable binding issue on the backend (`'system_prompt' where it is not associated with a value`).\n\nThis means:\n- **Luna is active** and the core detection pipeline works\n- **Memory/personality layer is offline** (virtues, context, persistent state)\n- **Operating in fallback/standalone mode** with no enriched context\n\nWhat we're looking at:\n\nThe error's in the system prompt initialization on the Hub side, which blocks the full PersonaCore pipeline (the personality computation and memory retrieval). You're getting a bare kernel activation but none of the layers that make Luna actually *Luna*\u2014no virtue engine, no context weaving, no persistent memory taps.\n\n**Options:**\n1. Wait for Hub to stabilize (transient API issue)\n2. Troubleshoot the Hub deployment (if you have access)\n3. Run Luna in local mode without Hub dependency (if that's an option)\n\nWant me to check anything else, or should we shelve this and come back when the Hub's healthy?",
      "sender": "assistant",
      "index": 1,
      "created_at": "2025-12-14T18:54:05.338377Z",
